My idea to make buying in the bazaar much, much easier and also making the sales bug obsolete:<br>
<br>
Implement a system so that players can reserve an item on the search menu. This removes it from the general market and greys it out in the seller's inventory for a certain amount of time. Only the person who reserved it can buy, and if they go over the time limit, it goes back up to the general market search function.<br>
<br>
Example:<br>
<br>
Player_01 types into the search query: Fighting Baton<br>
Seller_01 is selling it for 150pp<br>
Player_01 clicks the button on the lower right corner of the menu &quot;Reserve item&quot;<br>
The fighting baton for 150pp, upon refreshing the query, is no longer available.<br>
Now, say Buyer_02 was browsing and saw the FB for 150pp before refreshing the query.<br>
Buyer_02 clicks &quot;Reserve item&quot; but gets a message stating &quot;This item has already been reserved.&quot;<br>
Meanwhile, Player_01 goes to the bank and heads out to find Seller_01<br>
Buyer_03 is browsing Seller_01's wares.<br>
The FB shows in inventory, but it is greyed out and upon mousing over it displays the text &quot;Item reserved for x more minutes&quot;<br>
Player_01 finds Seller_01 and is able to purchase his reserved FB, no questions asked.<br>
<br>
<br>
